President Uhuru Kenyatta and opposition leader Raila Odinga have appointed fourteen advisers assist in uniting Kenyans under the building bridges initiative. They include; Adams Oloo, Agnes Kavindu, Florence Omose, Mzee James Matundura, Major rtd John Seii and Bishop Lawi Mathiu. Others are; hon Maison leshono, senator Mohamed Yusuf Haji, Morompi ole Ronkai, bishop Peter Njenga, Rose Museu, and Zeccheus Okoth "The 14 shall work under the direction of the building bridges initiative secretariat which is headed by ambassador Martin Kimani and Paul Mwangi." Read part of the statement signed by ambassador Kimani. The initiative was launched by the two leaders on March 9, 2018, to create a united nation for all Kenyans and future generations. Read : Uhuru, Raila enter pact to end ethnic tension and heal wounds Some of the issues that the advisers are expected to oversee include matters of ethnicity, exclusivity, lack of national ethos, devolution, divisive elections, safety and security, corruption, shared prosperity and rights and responsibilities. Also read : Raila took calculated risk to avert bloodshed - Salim Lone Click here for the latest political news